track_notes: This hike originates at the Ramsey Vista Campground which is about a 2.5 hour drive from Tucson. Take the Carr Peak Trail #17. Go past the cutoff to Carr Peak and continue to the Crest Trail #103 to the turnoff for Miller Peak. The hike is 5.64 miles one way with 2,865 ft of gross elevation gain and an average slope of 22 degrees. There are no trees at the summit so bring a mast.
track_title: Miller Peak from Ramsey Vista Campground

track_notes: This hike has more elevation gain but is shorter than the hike to Miller Peak originating at the Ramsey Vista Campground. Park at the Lutz Canyon Trailhead at GPS coordinates 31.3790,-110.2632. The hike was 3.95 miles one way on trails with gross elevation gain of 3,865 ft and average slope of 28 degrees. No trees at the summit so bring a mast.

This route is very long and quite challenging with considerable up and down.  My GPS measured 20.20 miles.  It would be very easy to add Carr Peak, W7A/CO-001 to the route as you go right past it, IF you have enough time and energy left!
track_title: Ramsey Peak and Miller Peak Loop

track_notes: This hike covers the first 7 miles of the Arizona Trail.  Park at the Montezuma Pass parking area.  You need to hike about 2 miles down to reach the Southern Terminus of the Arizona Trail, which is marked by a monument and fence at the US/Mexico border.  Then hike back up the same 2 miles - almost 900 feet of climb - to the parking area.  It isnt necessary to do this first 4 miles for the activation, but if you have never been to the beginning of the trail I highly recommend it.  The next 5 miles go up the Crest Trail (which is also the Arizona Trail) towards the summit.  There are steep sections, most of it is sun-exposed, but its a beautiful strenuous hike.  The final short approach to Miller Peak is a separate spur trail.  The summit is a rocky one with amazing views.  Nearby trees in the activation zone can be used for your antenna. The return hike is almost entirely downhill and will feel quite nice after all that climbing!
track_title: Arizona Trail Southern Terminus to Miller Peak
